GTK_IM_MODULE="xim" => use the X input method

http://unix.stackexchange.com/questions/39547/dead-compose-keys-not-working-in-gtk-apps-since-upgrade/65755#65755

    If you use an input module at the X11 level (eg, one defined by
    XMODIFIERS=…), then X11 doesn't handle dead keys nor compose anymore,
    it is up to the input module to do it.
    What you would need would be a way to switch between
    XMODIFIERS="@im=ibus" and XMODIFIERS="@im=none" (to let X11 do the work).
Note: "@im=none" is the default (=xim?), it handles the compose key by default.
Setting another im suppose that the im will handle the compose key.

http://unix.stackexchange.com/questions/260601/understanding-setting-up-different-input-methods
    If you want to explicitly disable any input method, use these settings:
    export GTK_IM_MODULE="gtk-im-context-simple"
    export QT_IM_MODULE="simple"
    An empty string works as well

    If GTK_IM_MODULE is not set, GTK selects a built-in IM on the basis of configurations in /etc/gtk-2.0/gtk.immodules. GTK 3.0 looks in /usr/lib/gtk-3.0/3.0.0/immodules.cache which is generated by gtk-query-immodule

    Now what about XIM? XIM is a pretty obsolete input method protocol
    which both ibus and fcitx implement for legacy support reasons only.
    There is no real reason why you would want to use XIM nowadays over any
    of those two. The only reason why you would want to set
    GTK_IM_MODULE="xim" is to override GTK's hardcoded ComposeKey settings.

https://wiki.archlinux.org/index.php/Internationalization#Input_methods_in_Xorg
gtk input module order:
- GTK_IM_MODULE environment variable
- XSETTINGS value of Gtk/IMModule

To prevent GTK+ from loading any IM modules
- GTK_IM_MODULE=""
- GTK_IM_MODULE="gtk-im-context-simple"

qt input module order: 
- QT_IM_MODULE environment variable
- XIM
To disable input method module loading in QT: export QT_IM_MODULE="simple". 

==========================================================
Ibus:
export GTK_IM_MODULE=ibus
export XMODIFIERS=@im=ibus
export QT_IM_MODULE=ibus
/usr/bin/ibus-daemon "--xim"

Uim:
export GTK_IM_MODULE=uim
export XMODIFIERS=@im=uim
export QT_IM_MODULE=uim

Uim
===

Latin characters: utilise compose
ELatin: plein de dead keys
m17n-fr-azerty: le clavier azerty
rfc1345: & est le raccourci
unicode: ^U et le numéro unicode
latn-pre: dead key puis key
latn-post: key puis dead key
phonetic: taper les caractères phonétiques
